## ðŸ”§ Troubleshooting

### Backend Issues
- Make sure all Python dependencies are installed: `pip install -r config/requirements.txt`
- Check that the `.env` file exists in the root directory
- Verify Walacor connection settings in `.env`

### Frontend Issues
- Make sure node_modules are installed: `cd frontend && npm install`
- Check that the backend is running on port 8000
- Verify CORS settings if you see connection errors

### Port Conflicts
- If port 8000 is in use, change it in `backend/start_server.py`
- If port 3000 is in use, Next.js will automatically use the next available port

